##The number says epidemic 0207: Epidemic Trend continues to slow down

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. "CAIJING" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was first published in 1998, adhering to the news concept of "independence, exclusiveness and originality" , and is known for authoritative, impartial and professional reporting, it is a must-read publication for policy-makers, researchers and managers in the field of politics and economics.

Figure / Fachen

By Michael R. mckee

1. Today in general:

As of 2400 hours on February 6,31 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps have reported 31,161 confirmed cases, 1,540 cured and discharged from hospitals, and 28,985 confirmed cases (including 4,821 severe cases) , according to the National Health Commission, there were 636 cumulative deaths and 26,359 suspected cases. A total of 314028 close contacts were traced and 186045 close contacts remained under medical observation. A total of 50 confirmed cases were reported from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan, including one death case in Hong Kong.

2. The number of newly diagnosed cases continues to decline

The number of newly confirmed cases in Hubei has fallen for the second day in a row. That is a remarkable result, given that it is struggling to digest the backlog of uncollected, untested cases. The non-hubei region has been stable for three consecutive days, which may mean that the non-hubei region is being tested for second-generation transmission of the virus.

3. The rate of increase in confirmed cases continues to decline

Some netizen thinks growth rate is affected by base number to increase substantially, can not explain a problem. In fact, the rate of change in the growth rate is an important parameter in forecasting trends, the base number is more reliable. Whether the growth rate is rising or falling makes a qualitative difference. The continued decline in Hubei's growth rate gives us hope. This means that the doubling of the time for the confirmation of cases is expected to extend from three or four days in the previous phase to more than one week. The doubling of cases in non-hubei areas will be extended to more than 10 days.

4. The stock of suspected cases to be screened has risen slightly

5. Close contacts tracking dynamics and stocks

This tracking coefficient can be intuitively understood as the average number of people tracked down for each confirmed case. It is not hard to see that the non-hubei tracking far greater than Hubei. We have increased confidence in the prevention and control of non-hubei areas and have also felt the pressures facing Hubei. We're also seeing a leveling off in the number of observers who are still tracking. This stock data is also a stabilizing signal.

Note: Close contact tracking factor daily close contact increment / number of newly confirmed cases per day

6. Cure far more people than die

The cumulative number of cured discharged patients and the number of deaths continued to widen the gap. Hubei also continued to improve three days after the number of cured people reversed to exceed the number of deaths from illness.

Summary: Many people think that the inflection point is at the top of the mountain, but the mathematical definition of the inflection point is actually in the mountainside. There is no peak until there is an inflection point in the mountainside. Here we use common sense language to use the "inflection point. ". So for now, let's just say the epidemic is slowing down, and let's hope the numbers are clearer. Let's go, people!
